  "prompt": "What is the meaning of stress?",
  "response": "Stress is a physical, mental, and emotional response to challenging or demanding situations. It can be defined in several ways:\n\n1. Psychological definition:\n- A feeling of emotional or physical tension\n- A reaction to pressure or challenges in life\n- A state of mental or emotional strain\n\n2. Physiological definition:\n- The body's natural response to perceived threats or challenges\n- A cascade of hormonal and neurological changes\n- Activation of the \"fight or flight\" response\n\n3. Common characteristics of stress:\n- Can be caused by work, relationships, financial issues, or personal challenges\n- Triggers the release of stress hormones like cortisol and adrenaline\n- Can be acute (short-term) or chronic (long-term)\n\n4. Types of stress:\n- Positive stress (eustress): Motivating and can improve performance\n- Negative stress (distress): Harmful and can impact mental and physical health\n\n5. Potential effects:\n- Increased heart rate\n- Heightened alertness\n- Muscle tension\n- Potential long-term health consequences if not managed\n\nUnderstanding and managing stress is crucial for maintaining overall well-being and mental health.",
